<p>Hi, I’m Dan Shiebler. I like math, history podcasts, fantasy novels, riding my bicycle, and traveling. I live in NYC.</p>

<p>Right now I work as the Head of Machine Learning at <a href="https://abnormalsecurity.com/">Abnormal Security</a>. Previously, I led the Web Ads Machine Learning team at Twitter. Before that I worked as a Staff ML Engineer at <a href="https://cortex.twitter.com/">Twitter Cortex</a> and a Senior Data Scientist at <a href="https://gotruemotion.com/">TrueMotion</a>.</p>

<p>I’ve also spent some time in Academia. My PhD research at the University of Oxford focused on applications of Category Theory to Machine Learning (advised by <a href="https://www.cs.ox.ac.uk/people/jeremy.gibbons/">Jeremy Gibbons</a> and <a href="https://www.th-deg.de/en/Cezar-Ionescu-Fakult%C3%A4t%20Angewandte%20Informatik-Professoren/-innen-1975">Cezar Ionescu</a>). Before that I worked as a Computer Vision Researcher at the <a href="http://serre-lab.clps.brown.edu/">Serre Lab</a>.</p>

<p>I Tweet <a href="https://twitter.com/dshieble">@dshieble</a> and my <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/dan-shiebler-10219b42/">linkedin</a> and <a href="https://github.com/dshieble">github</a> are usually somewhat up-to-date.</p>
